---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Introduction" description="Introduction to Marrow UI and its design philosophy" activeSection="introduction">
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Introduction</h1>
          <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-muted-foreground">The philosophy behind Marrow UI and why it exists.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mw-separator"></div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Why Marrow UI?</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Most modern UI kits are built for React. If you're using any other technology &mdash; whether it's a server-rendered framework like Django, Laravel, or Rails, or a static site generator like Hugo or Eleventy &mdash; your options are limited.</p>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Marrow UI solves this by providing a complete set of UI components that use:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
            <li><strong>Tailwind CSS</strong> for styling &mdash; utility-first, customizable, no CSS-in-JS</li>
            <li><strong>Alpine.js</strong> for interactivity &mdash; lightweight, declarative, lives in your HTML</li>
            <li><strong>CSS custom properties</strong> for theming &mdash; one config file controls everything</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">How It Works</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">Marrow UI is a copy-paste component library. Each component in the documentation includes:</p>
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
            <li><strong>Live preview</strong> &mdash; See the component in action</li>
            <li><strong>Source code</strong> &mdash; Copy the HTML directly</li>
            <li><strong>Variants</strong> &mdash; Different styles and configurations</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">You include the base CSS file and Alpine.js in your project, then copy and paste the component HTML wherever you need it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Design Principles</h2>
          <div class="grid gap-4">
            <div class="mw-card">
              <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold mb-1">No Framework Lock-in</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Components are plain HTML. They work with any backend, any templating engine, any static site generator.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mw-card">
              <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold mb-1">Opinionated Defaults</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Every component looks great out of the box. The config file gives you control when you need it.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mw-card">
              <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold mb-1">Progressive Enhancement</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Components that don't need JavaScript work without it. Alpine.js adds interactivity where it's needed.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mw-card">
              <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold mb-1">One Config, Full Control</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Colors, spacing, radius, fonts, shadows, transitions, compactness &mdash; all from one file.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">How Marrow UI Compares</h2>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="mw-table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Feature</th>
                  <th>React UI Kits</th>
                  <th>Marrow UI</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>Framework</td>
                  <td class="text-muted-foreground">React</td>
                  <td>HTML + Alpine.js</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Styling</td>
                  <td class="text-muted-foreground">Tailwind CSS</td>
                  <td>Tailwind CSS</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Theming</td>
                  <td class="text-muted-foreground">CSS Variables</td>
                  <td>CSS Variables + Config file</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Installation</td>
                  <td class="text-muted-foreground">CLI + npm</td>
                  <td>Copy & paste</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Build Step</td>
                  <td class="text-muted-foreground">Required</td>
                  <td>Optional</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Bundle Size</td>
                  <td class="text-muted-foreground">React + deps</td>
                  <td>Alpine.js (~15KB)</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

</DocsLayout>
